source.name: Federal Supply Classification Cataloging (H2) Search Tool
source.description: The Federal Supply Classification (FSC) Search Tool is a logistics tool developed to search for items of supply identified under the Federal Catalog System.   The structure of the FSC, as presently established, consists of 78 groups, which are subdivided into over 600 classes.  The tool allows for searches by entering the FSC, FSG or Title. Results of specific searches are output on a Results List, identifying FSC or FSG and Title. From here the highlighted item is displayed, providing all related data elements.
